biolockj.module

Class BioModuleImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • biolockj.module.BioModuleImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BioModule, Comparable<BioModule>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Email, ImportMetadata, ScriptModuleImpl

    public abstract class BioModuleImpl
extends Object
implements BioModule, Comparable<BioModule>
    Superclass for standard BioModules (classifiers, parsers, etc). Sets standard behavior for many of the BioModule interface methods.

        public final String getPropDefault(String prop)
        Description copied from interface: BioModule
        If a property is null based on the config files (including all defaults and standard.properties) but a module is passed to the Config class as the context for getting that module, the Config class can query the module for a value for the property. In general, this is used for the properties defined in this module, but it CAN also be used for general properties.

      • isValidInputModule

        public boolean isValidInputModule(BioModule module)
        In the early stages of the pipeline, starting with the very 1st module ImportMetadata, most modules expect sequence files as input. This method returns false if the previousModule only produced a new metadata file, such as ImportMetadata or RegisterNumReads. When getInputFiles() is called, this method determines if the previousModule output is valid input for the current BioModule. The default implementation of this method returns FALSE if the previousModule only generates a new metadata file.
        Specified by:
        isValidInputModule in interface BioModule
        Parameters:
        module - BioModule that ran before the current BioModule
        Returns:
        boolean TRUE if the previousModule output is acceptable input for the current BioModule
